<DocsLayout title="Assisted Argumentation" description="Build arguments from jurisprudence, grounding, and reasoning chains.">
  <h1>Assisted Argumentation</h1>
  <span class="badge badge-dev">in development</span>

  <p>
    Argumentation in sens.legal is no longer framed as a closed "optimal argument"
    score. The current direction is to assemble assisted answers with relevant
    jurisprudence, legislative context, doctrinal artifacts, and an auditable
    reasoning chain.
  </p>

  <h2>How it works</h2>

  <ol>
    <li>Valter retrieves relevant jurisprudence through graph-led retrieval</li>
    <li>The reasoning chain explains why each decision belongs in the answer</li>
    <li>Leci can add legislative grounding when the question depends on statutory text</li>
    <li>Douto can provide doctrinal artifacts when a handoff is available</li>
    <li>Juca will turn that material into human-facing briefing and canvas flows (progressive briefing is the next product milestone)</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>Example</h2>

  <h4>Request</h4>

<pre><code>POST /api/v1/graph/optimal-argument
Content-Type: application/json

{"{"}
  "category": "Consumer Law",
  "question": "which grounds are worth advancing in a defective product case?"
{"}"}</code></pre>

  <h4>Response</h4>

<pre><code>{"{"}
  "thesis_candidates": [
    {"{"}
      "thesis": "Strict liability of the supplier",
      "supporting_decisions": ["REsp 1.234.567/SP"],
      "legislation": ["Art. 12 do CDC", "Art. 14 do CDC"],
      "why_it_matters": "recurring criterion in analogous cases"
    {"}"}
  ],
  "reasoning_chain": ["relevant facts", "applied criterion", "cited precedents"],
  "grounding_sources": ["jurisprudence", "legislation"]
{"}"}</code></pre>

  <h2>What makes it different</h2>

  <p>
    The answer stops being a mysterious score and becomes a set of explained
    grounds. The value lies in the traceability between the question, the retrieved
    jurisprudence, the applicable statutes, and the reasoning that connects them.
  </p>

  <h2>Available via</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><a href="/projects/juca">Juca</a> for the briefing and argument-building experience</li>
    <li><a href="/api/rest">Valter REST API gateway</a></li>
    <li><a href="/api/mcp">Valter MCP gateway</a></li>
  </ul>
